quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,123,"O you who have believed, fight the ones of the steadfast disbelievers who border on you and let them find in you (a) harshness; and know that Allah is with the pious"
  9,124,"And whenever a s?rah is sent down, then of them are the ones who say, \"Whichever of you has this increased him in belief?\" So, as for the ones who have believed, then it has increased them in belief, and they are glad at the tidings"
  9,125,"And as for the ones in whose hearts is sickness, then it increases them in abomination upon their abomination, and they die while they are disbelievers"
  9,126,And do they not see that they are tempted every season once or twice? (Yet) they do not repent thereafter nor do they constantly remember
  9,127,"And whenever a s?rah is sent down, they look one at another, (Literally: some of them looked at some \"others\") \"Does anyone ever see you?\" Then they turn about. Allah has turned their hearts about, for that they are people who do not comprehend"
  9,128,"Indeed there has already come to you a Messenger from (among) yourselves. Mighty (i.e., burdensome) to him is whatever distresses you. Most eager is he for your (welfare), to the believers (he is) constantly compassionate, constantly merciful"
  9,129,"So, in case they turn away, then say, \" Allah is enough (Reckoner) for me. There is no god except He. On Him I have put my trust; He is the Lord of the Magnificent Throne"